Introduce the concepts of an "idea" and of type classes.

Introduce a "trajectory" concept into the database, so that results produced from the same chat history belong to the same trajectory.

Generate a paper from the verified development.

Introduce the progress note.

Implement the ideation skill which is only triggered within a side task.

A `VERIFIED` marker is usable only when it matches the current cached statement, dependency snapshot, and verification record.

A proof block must immediately follow its theorem.

Provide a skill that helps the user create the main theorem.

Support conditional development, building on and writing a paper from certain assumed results.

Write clear help text for every command.

Do not over-design DISPROVED: it is just a label, and whatever it depends on can be written freely; a DISPROVED entry need not give a counterexample or a reverse proof, since a clear intuition is enough.

In README.md, separate the human-facing content from the AI-facing content, and add prompts for automatic pushing and automatic updating.

Decide whether to package this as a plugin installable from a marketplace.

The verifier need not scrutinize stale changes too strictly, and it may refer to the previous historical version.

A "paper" verifies correctness while "notes" verify readability, so notes require each definition to cite enough examples beneath it.

Use GitHub Actions to test each installation method.

Write documentation and review the skill's AGENTS.md.

Make inspect print its running time, or set a time budget and return control to the AI whenever it is exceeded.

Tune the verifier prompt well and add enough settings, such as reasoning effort and whether tools are allowed.

Tell the agent/user that using this is like learning a new programming language: `check` is the debugger, and writing proofs is like programming, where you write a little and then check.

Clearly explain to the AI the rationale behind each change and how far a single change reaches, and remind it to watch the verifier cost.
